					<msContents>
						<summary>A lacunose inscription, listing several endowments: an undated hereditary land endowment for singing (<foreign>tēci pāṭu</foreign>) before the Lord Tiruviṭaimarutuṭaiyār at the time assembly hall <foreign>tiruvōlakkam</foreign> and another land endowment dated to the seventh regnal year of Parakesarivarman to various gods at Tiruviṭaimarutu, including Viṣṇu of the Talaikkōliviṇṇakar.</summary>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<p>
								Only Fragment 1 refers to the singing as <foreign>tēciy pāṭu</foreign>, and only one instance we find <foreign>tēciya pāṭu</foreign>. Fragment 2 does not record this singing. 
							</p>
							<p/>
						</handDesc>
					</physDesc>
